      title: 'Local LLM One-Click Installers: Ollama vs LM Studio vs Jan AI vs GPT4All Compared',
      seoTitle: 'Ollama, LM Studio, Jan AI, GPT4All: Which to Choose?',
      intro: '**Ollama, LM Studio, Jan AI, and GPT4All each install in under 5 minutes and handle model downloads automatically вҖ” no manual llama.cpp compilation, no weight conversion, no configuration files.** As of April 2026, all four tools use llama.cpp as their inference backend and support the same GGUF model format, meaning you can switch between them without re-downloading models. The choice comes down to interface preference: Ollama for developers who want a CLI and API, LM Studio for a polished GUI with Hugging Face search, Jan AI for maximum privacy and open-source auditability, GPT4All for the simplest possible one-click desktop experience.',
