          title: 'How Does Running Local LLMs on a Laptop Protect Your Privacy?',
          content: [
            '**EU / GDPR**: A laptop running local LLMs is the most privacy-preserving AI configuration available. No prompt text, context, or output leaves the device вҖ” GDPR Article 46 transfer mechanisms are not required. For EU professionals handling personal data (medical, legal, financial), a MacBook Pro M3 or M4 with 18вҖ“36 GB unified memory is the recommended configuration for local inference with sensitive content. German BSI guidelines recommend local inference for AI systems processing sensitive personal data in professional contexts.',
            '**Japan (METI)**: METI AI Governance Guidelines require organizations to document where AI inference occurs. A laptop running Ollama locally satisfies this requirement for individual professional use вҖ” all inference is traceable to the device and model version. Japanese professionals commonly use LLaMA 3.1 7B via Ollama on M-series MacBooks for zero-egress sensitive document processing.',
            '**China**: China\'s Data Security Law (ж•°жҚ®е®үе…Ёжі•) restricts certain data categories from leaving approved infrastructure. A laptop running Qwen2.5 7B locally via Ollama satisfies this requirement for individual use cases вҖ” Qwen2.5 processes Chinese-language content 30вҖ“40% more token-efficiently than Western-trained models on the same hardware.',
          ],
