      intro: 'LLM quantization reduces model weight precision from 32-bit or 16-bit floats to 4-bit or 8-bit integers, cutting RAM requirements by 50вҖ“75% with minimal quality loss. Q4_K_M is the standard recommended quantization for local inference вҖ” it reduces a 7B model from ~14 GB to ~4.5 GB while retaining 97вҖ“99% of the original model quality on standard benchmarks.',
